# pcli — HPE ProLiant unified CLI

**pcli** is a unified CLI for HPE ProLiant environments. It lets you retrieve and inspect server inventory and details across **iLO**, **HPE GreenLake COM**, and **HPE OneView** — and includes a built-in tool to fetch and read HPE ProLiant **QuickSpec** documents directly from the terminal.

Whether you manage a handful of bare-metal servers or a large fleet across multiple management platforms, `pcli` gives you a single consistent interface. Query firmware versions across hundreds of iLO nodes in seconds, browse your GreenLake device inventory, inspect servers managed by HPE OneView, or pull up the latest QuickSpec for any ProLiant model — all without opening a browser or logging into a GUI.

![pcli demo](docs/demo.svg)

## Installation

### Windows (no Python required)

1. Download the latest `proliant-cli-windows.zip` from the [Releases](../../releases/latest) page
2. Extract the zip to a folder (e.g. `C:\Tools\pcli\`)
3. Open PowerShell, `cd` into that folder, and run:

```powershell
.\pcli --version
```

pcli will offer to add itself to your PATH so you can run `pcli` from anywhere.

### From source (Linux / macOS / WSL)

```bash
git clone <repo>
cd proliant-cli
pip install -e ".[all]"
```

## Usage

```
pcli ilo <command>       # Direct iLO Redfish management
pcli com <command>       # HPE GreenLake / Compute Ops Management
pcli oneview <command>   # HPE OneView management
pcli qs <command>        # HPE ProLiant QuickSpec reader
```

### iLO commands

```bash
pcli ilo init                              # Create starter hosts-ilo.ini config
pcli ilo list firmwares                    # Firmware summary across all hosts
pcli ilo list ilo                          # iLO firmware versions
pcli ilo list network                      # NIC firmware versions
pcli ilo list storage                      # Storage controllers + drives
pcli ilo list bios                         # BIOS/System ROM versions
pcli ilo list cpu                          # CPU models + microcode
pcli ilo list memory                       # DIMM details
pcli ilo list full                         # Full firmware inventory
pcli ilo upgrade --host myilo              # Auto-upgrade all firmware from HPE SDR
pcli ilo upgrade --host myilo --dry-run    # Preview without changes
pcli ilo upgrade --host myilo --reboot     # Upgrade and reboot
```

### COM commands

```bash
pcli com login                             # Login to HPE GreenLake (Okta or API client)
pcli com logout                            # Remove cached credentials
pcli com get devices                       # List all devices in workspace
pcli com get devices --type COMPUTE        # Filter by type
pcli com get workspaces                    # List workspaces
pcli com use workspace <name>              # Switch active workspace
```

### OneView commands

```bash
pcli oneview list servers                  # List all managed servers
pcli oneview list firmware                 # Show firmware inventory
pcli oneview list networks                 # List ethernet networks
pcli oneview list networksets              # List network sets
pcli oneview list uplinksets               # List uplink sets
pcli oneview list server-profiles          # List server profiles
pcli oneview describe server <name>        # Detailed info for a server
pcli oneview report memory                 # Memory DIMM part-number breakdown
```

### QuickSpec commands

```bash
pcli qs list --model dl380gen11            # Find QuickSpec revisions for a model
pcli qs describe <doc-id>                  # Read a QuickSpec as formatted markdown
pcli qs diff <doc-id1> <doc-id2>           # Compare two QuickSpec versions
```

## Updating

```bash
pcli update                                # Self-update to the latest release
```

## Config files

- iLO hosts: `hosts-ilo.ini` (in current directory — run `pcli ilo init` to create)
- COM credentials: `~/.config/pcli/com/credentials.yml`
- COM token cache: `~/.config/pcli/com/token.json`
